    "start_blocks": "//Hey! I should comment my code!\n//This is a Proof of Concept level that shows a few things: drag-and-drop in App Lab, and Validation\n\n\n//This function is necessary for Validation to work in App Lab.\n//This thread has a bunch of historical knowledge: https://codedotorg.slack.com/archives/C1B3PNDL7/p1662482867134019\n//But essentially, the way validation works in App Lab is it relies on this running log of every command that runs in the program is kept. \n//You can access it in the developer console with Applab.currentExecutionLog\n//And then the validation works by comparing the log with an expected output.\n//So in this case, I'm making a success function and only calling it when I'm sure the level is complete\n//And then if you look at the \"Edit\" screen for this level in the validation section, you'll see a JSON object that essentially checks that this function was called at least 1 time\n//This makes the actual levelbuilding-validation pretty easy and could be re-used across different levels\n//And the actual validation logic can happen inside this starter code, which is what I do later in the program.\nfunction success() {\n  console.log(\"success\");\n}\n\nfunction clicked() {\n  console.log(\"clicked at least once!\");\n}\n\n//A lot of the dragging logic came from this post on the forum: https://forum.code.org/t/is-there-a-way-to-code-a-drag-and-drop-behavior-on-an-image/13037/6\n//And then this project someone posted later with improvements on Baker's initial post: https://studio.code.org/projects/applab/g3Q6so46nK07lxfzyjF2waEkbpsJ6Rs5oFX3Meb18PE/view\n//One key detail is that in design mode, dragging works better on buttons than images. So all of the draggable elements are actually button design elements\n//The rest of the code is modeled after what the program above did, but abstracts some global variables to objects instead.\nvar dragObj = {\n  state: false,\n  curDraggable: null,\n  xOffset: 0,\n  yOffset: 0\n};\n\nfunction resetDragObj() {\n  dragObj.state = false;\n  dragObj.curDraggable = null;\n  dragObj.xOffset = 0;\n  dragObj.yOffset = 0;\n}\n\n//NOTE: in Design Mode, these are actually buttons due to an interaction with image types and dragging\nvar SOLUTIONARRAY = [\n\t[\"dragA\", \"labelA\"],\n\t[\"dragB\", \"labelB\"]\n];\n\n//var DRAGGABLEARRAY = [\"imgA\", \"imgB\", \"imgC\", \"imgD\"];\nvar DRAGGABLEARRAY = [];\n\nfor(var i = 0; i < SOLUTIONARRAY.length; i++) {\n  DRAGGABLEARRAY.push(SOLUTIONARRAY[i][0]);\n}\n\n\n\n\n//This is just a clever way to generalize making onEvents for each draggable element.\nfor(var i = 0; i < DRAGGABLEARRAY.length; i++) {\n  var curDraggable = DRAGGABLEARRAY[i];\n  \n  //visual change to show is draggable\n  onEvent(curDraggable, \"mouseover\", function(e) {\n    //Because of how events calculate the ID, I need to use the event ID instead of the curDraggable variable\n    setProperty(e.targetId, \"border-width\", 2);\n  });\n  onEvent(curDraggable, \"mouseout\", function(e) {\n    setProperty(e.targetId, \"border-width\", 0);\n  });\n  \n  // start dragging currrent element\n  onEvent(curDraggable, \"mousedown\", function(e) {\n    console.log(e);\n    dragObj.state = true;\n    dragObj.curDraggable = e.targetId;\n    dragObj.xOffset = e.x - getProperty(e.targetId, \"x\");\n    dragObj.yOffset = e.y - getProperty(e.targetId, \"y\");\n  });\n}\n\nonEvent(\"screen1\", \"mouseup\", function() {\n  resetDragObj();\n});\n\nonEvent(\"screen1\", \"mousemove\", function(e){\n  if(dragObj.state == true){\n    //console.log(dragObj.curDraggable);\n    var newX = e.x - dragObj.xOffset;\n    var newY = e.y - dragObj.yOffset;\n    setPosition(dragObj.curDraggable, newX, newY);\n  }\n});\n\n//Checks if the center (x, y) of id1 is inside the bounding box of id2\nfunction checkCenterInside(id1, id2) {\n  var id1Obj = {};\n  id1Obj.x = getProperty(id1, \"x\");\n  id1Obj.y = getProperty(id1, \"y\");\n  id1Obj.width = getProperty(id1, \"width\");\n  id1Obj.height = getProperty(id1, \"height\");\n  id1Obj.centerX = id1Obj.x + (id1Obj.width / 2);\n  id1Obj.centerY = id1Obj.y + (id1Obj.height / 2);\n  \n  var id2Obj = {};\n  id2Obj.x = getProperty(id2, \"x\");\n  id2Obj.y = getProperty(id2, \"y\");\n  id2Obj.width = getProperty(id2, \"width\");\n  id2Obj.height = getProperty(id2, \"height\");\n  id2Obj.centerX = id2Obj.x + (id2Obj.width / 2);\n  id2Obj.centerY = id2Obj.y + (id2Obj.height / 2);\n  \n  if((id1Obj.centerX > id2Obj.x && id1Obj.centerX < (id2Obj.x + id2Obj.width)) && (id1Obj.centerY > id2Obj.y && id1Obj.centerY < (id2Obj.y + id2Obj.height))) {\n    return true;\n  } else {\n    return false;\n  }\n}\n\n//This is my validation logic. When it's all true, I call \"success\", which is what the levelbuilder validation is looking for.\nonEvent(\"checkButton\", \"click\", function( ) {\n  clicked();\n\tvar correct = 0;\n\tfor(var i = 0; i < SOLUTIONARRAY.length; i++) {\n\t  if(checkCenterInside(SOLUTIONARRAY[i][0], SOLUTIONARRAY[i][1])) {\n\t    console.log(\"Success: \" + SOLUTIONARRAY[i][0] + \" is inside \" + SOLUTIONARRAY[i][1]);\n\t    correct += 1;\n\t  } else {\n\t    console.log(\"FAIL: \" + SOLUTIONARRAY[i][0] + \" is not inside \" + SOLUTIONARRAY[i][1]);\n\t  }\n\t}\n\tif(correct >= SOLUTIONARRAY.length) {\n\t  setProperty(\"feedbackImg\", \"image\", \"icon://fa-check-square\");\n\t  setProperty(\"feedbackImg\", \"icon-color\", \"#0ed220\");\n\t  success();\n\t} else {\n\t  setProperty(\"feedbackImg\", \"image\", \"icon://fa-times-circle\");\n\t  setProperty(\"feedbackImg\", \"icon-color\", \"#d20e47\");\n\t  partialSuccess();\n\t}\n});\n\nfunction partialSuccess() {\n  console.log(\"partial correct\");\n}",
    "start_html": "<div id=\"designModeViz\" class=\"appModern clip-content\" data-radium=\"true\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 450px; display: none;\"><div class=\"screen\" tabindex=\"1\" data-theme=\"default\" id=\"screen1\" style=\"display: block; height: 450px; width: 600px; left: 0px; top: 0px; position: absolute; z-index: 0; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><img src=\"/level_starter_assets/musiclab-hotspot-functions-test/musiclab-hotspot-test.png\" data-canonical-image-url=\"image://musiclab-hotspot-test.png\" data-image-type=\"file\" data-object-fit=\"contain\" id=\"image1\" style=\"height: 375px; width: 545px; border-style: solid; border-width: 0px; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); border-radius: 0px; position: absolute; left: 0px; top: 0px; margin: 0px;\"><label style=\"margin: 0px; line-height: 1; overflow: hidden; overflow-wrap: break-word; max-width: 320px; border-style: solid; text-rendering: optimizespeed; color: rgb(77, 87, 95); background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-color: rgb(77, 87, 95); border-radius: 0px; border-width: 0px; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Gadget, sans-serif; padding: 2px 15px; width: 90px; height: 30px; position: absolute; left: 10px; top: 180px; font-size: 70px; text-align: center;\" id=\"labelB\"></label><label style=\"margin: 0px; line-height: 1; overflow: hidden; overflow-wrap: break-word; max-width: 320px; border-style: solid; text-rendering: optimizespeed; color: rgb(77, 87, 95); background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-color: rgb(77, 87, 95); border-radius: 0px; border-width: 0px; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Gadget, sans-serif; padding: 2px 15px; width: 125px; height: 35px; position: absolute; left: 265px; top: 10px; font-size: 70px; text-align: center;\" id=\"labelA\"></label><button id=\"checkButton\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border-style: solid; height: 35px; width: 150px; background-color: rgb(255, 164, 0); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border-color: rgb(77, 87, 95); border-radius: 4px; border-width: 1px; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Gadget, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; position: absolute; left: 435px; top: 405px;\">Check Answers</button><button id=\"dragA\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border-style: solid; height: 25px; width: 65px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); border-color: rgb(77, 87, 95); border-radius: 0px; border-width: 2px; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Gadget, sans-serif; position: absolute; left: 475px; top: 5px; background-size: contain; background-position: 50% 50%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-image: url(&quot;https://levelbuilder-studio.code.org/blockly/media/1x1.gif&quot;); font-size: 19px;\" data-canonical-image-url=\"\" data-image-type=\"default\">A</button><button id=\"dragB\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border-style: solid; height: 25px; width: 65px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); border-color: rgb(77, 87, 95); border-radius: 0px; border-width: 2px; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Gadget, sans-serif; position: absolute; left: 475px; top: 40px; background-size: contain; background-position: 50% 50%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-image: url(&quot;https://levelbuilder-studio.code.org/blockly/media/1x1.gif&quot;); font-size: 19px;\" data-canonical-image-url=\"\" data-image-type=\"default\">B</button><img data-canonical-image-url=\"icon://fa-question-circle\" data-image-type=\"icon\" data-object-fit=\"contain\" id=\"feedbackImg\" style=\"height: 65px; width: 65px; border-style: solid; border-width: 0px; border-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); border-radius: 0px; position: absolute; left: 365px; top: 385px; margin: 0px;\" data-icon-color=\"#000000\"></div></div>",
    "long_instructions": "Drag the \"A\" to the place where a function is **Defined**\r\n\r\nDrag the \"B\" to the place where a function is **Called**",
